---
// Internal review banner — flags content that needs human verification before
// launch. Controlled by REVIEW_MODE in src/lib/site.ts; set that to false (or
// delete this component's usage) to remove it everywhere before deploy.
import { url } from '../lib/site';
---
<aside class="review-notice" role="note" aria-label="Internal review notice">
  <p class="review-notice-tag">⚠ Internal review — not for public release</p>
  <p>
    This is a draft for the program committee. The following need a human
    accuracy/recency pass before launch:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Required readings.</strong> The citation lists (see the
      <a href={`${url('curriculum')}#required-readings`}>curriculum readings</a>)
      are carried from the program materials and several look out of date or
      incorrect — verify every
      citation, that it is the intended reading, and that each link resolves.
      <em>Day 2</em>’s “datasets list” and <em>Day 4</em>’s “instructor’s pick”
      are placeholders.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Curriculum & schedule.</strong> Authored from the finalized program
      materials — confirm day themes, the five-block / closing-small-group
      structure, and all times against the official schedule.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Instructors.</strong> Day/role come from the source data; some
      bios, links, awards, and press were assembled programmatically — verify
      each, and confirm day assignments (source session times were stale and are
      not shown).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Students.</strong> Bios, links, awards, press, and taglines were
      assembled/drafted programmatically — verify each profile.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Workshop notebooks & Project Workbook.</strong> Drafts — review and
      expand before use.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Slide decks.</strong> Tentative and actively being revised in the
      companion repository.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Still TBD:</strong> Day 5 fireside clinician/patient guest; Day 6
      panelists; final contact email and site URL.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="review-notice-foot">
    To remove this banner, set <code>REVIEW_MODE = false</code> in
    <code>src/lib/site.ts</code>.
  </p>
</aside>
